ILLEGAL connections have claimed the lives of four people in Mpumalanga. The first incident was reported last Thursday where a teenage girl (16), who was with her boyfriend at the time, stepped on wet electricity cables. She was electrocuted and died instantly. In a separate incident, another victim was electrocuted while trying to fix an electric fault. Then a 36-year-old woman from Kamaqhekeza was electrocuted while working her field. The victim had burnt bruises on her arm. She was taken to hospital, where she succumbed to her injuries. You must be SIGNED IN to read comments  Meanwhile, a 12-year-old boy from Kamhlushwa died after he was electrocuted by cables while he had been sent to a neighbourâ€™s house. Police spokesman Brigadier Selvy Mohlala has since called on community members to refrain from doing illegal connections as more lives might be lost.